  <static seed="66" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/Factoring/factoring80.pg">
    <statement><p>Factor the given polynomial.</p>
<p><m>{16y-10y^{2}+6y^{3}}=</m> <fillin characters="19" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>2y\mathopen{}\left(8-5y+3y^{2}\right)</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>The greatest common factor is <m>2y</m>, so we can factor the polynomial as follows:</p>
<p><m>{16y-10y^{2}+6y^{3}}={2y\mathopen{}\left(8-5y+3y^{2}\right)}</m></p>
</solution>
